data.text:
New York: G.P. Putnam's Sons, 1970. First edition and first printing. Hardcover. A later novel from the author of "The Moon is a Harsh Mistress," "Stranger in a Strange Land" and numerous other classics. A clean near fine copy in cloth boards and in a very good plus dust jacket with a tiny chip to the top of the spine and with some other small edge tears and some light wear as well. Still, a pleasing copy of a book that is very prone to wear.

Item #192846
